      "I performed a web search for \"AI IDE launch February 2025 Cursor Windsurf alternative\" but the search results don't show any specific AI IDE that launched in February 2025. Here's what I found:\n\n## Current AI IDE Landscape (2025-2026)\n\nThe search results show the main AI IDEs that developers are comparing:\n\n### **Top AI IDEs:**\n\n1. **Cursor** (by Anysphere)\n   - AI-native IDE built as a VS Code fork\n   - Known for project-level context understanding\n   - ~$20/month for Pro version\n   - Composer feature for multi-file editing\n\n2. **Windsurf** (by Codeium)\n   - AI-native IDE with \"Flow\" mode for seamless collaboration\n   - Around $10-15/month for Pro\n   - Cascade agent mode with deep context understanding\n   - More affordable than Cursor\n\n3. **Other Notable Tools:**\n   - **GitHub Copilot** - ~$10/month, best for GitHub ecosystem integration\n   - **Zed** - Rust-based, real-time collaboration, free + $20/month\n   - **PearAI** - Open-source Cursor alternative\n   - **Trae** - Free, Chinese-optimized (ByteDance)\n\n## What the Search Revealed:\n\nThe search results focus on **comparisons** between existing tools (Cursor vs. Windsurf vs. Copilot) rather than any new February 2025 launch. The content is primarily from late 2025 and early 2026, discussing these established tools.\n\n**Would you like me to search more specifically?** For example:\n- A particular company name or product name?\n- Recent AI IDE announcements or funding news?\n- Open-source alternatives to Cursor/Windsurf?\n- A specific feature or capability you're looking for?\n\nLet me know what specific information you're trying to find, and I can refine the search!"
