ejin.cn/post/7553569648132407339\"},{\"title\":\"Qwen Code：基于大模型的终端智能编码交互工具\",\"url\":\"https://m.toutiao.com/a7552720381497360922/\"},{\"title\":\"Qwen Code v0.0.8 重磅发布：深度集成 VS Code\",\"url\":\"https://blog.csdn.net/Sammyyyyy/article/details/151075977\"},{\"title\":\"阿里云通义千问 Qwen Code 宣布每日可免费运行 2000 次\",\"url\":\"https://baijiahao.baidu.com/s?id=1839989745980727740\"},{\"title\":\"qwen-code CLI宣布每天免费2000次请求！ - 前沿快讯\",\"url\":\"https://linux.do/t/topic/852820\"}]\n\nBased on my search results for \"Qwen Code\" on GitHub, here's what I found:\n\n## Qwen Code - Terminal AI Coding Agent\n\n**Repository:** https://github.com/QwenLM/qwen-code\n\n### Overview\nQwen Code is an **open-source AI coding agent that lives in your terminal**. It's a command-line AI workflow tool specifically optimized for the Qwen3-Coder series models.\n\n### Key Details\n\n**Current Status (as of February 2026):**\n- ⭐ **18,822 stars** on GitHub (as of Feb 19, 2026)\n- 📈 Trending with +95 recent stars\n- **Actively maintained** with recent commits\n\n**About the Tool:**\n- Command-line interface (CLI) AI programming assistant\n- Forked from Gemini CLI and enhanced for Qwen models\n- Supports **code understanding, editing, and generation** at the repository level\n- Can automate Git tasks, refactor code, generate tests, and audit security\n- Works with large codebases through semantic understanding\n\n**Installation:**\n```bash\nnpm install -g @qwen-code/qwen-code@latest\nqwen\n```\n\n**Key Features:**\n- Repository-level code analysis and understanding\n- Semantic code editing and refactoring\n- Automated Git operations\n- Supports multiple models (Qwen3.5-Plus, Qwen3-Coder-Next, etc.)\n- Compatible with OpenAI SDK format\n- Multi-modal capabilities (supports images with newer models)\n\n**Recent Context (February 2026):**\n- Qwen Code has been highlighted alongside the February 2026 launch of **Qwen Coding Plan** subscription service\n- Integrated with the new **Qwen3.5** and **Qwen3-Coder-Next** models released in February 2026\n- Listed in the **Agent Client Protocol (ACP) registry** as an open-source AI coding agent\n\nThe project appears to be one of the leading open-source alternatives to tools like Claude Code and Cursor, specifically designed for terminal-based AI-assisted development workflows.\n\n\nREMINDER: You MUST include the sources above in your response to the user using markdown hyperlinks."
