智能Agents ...\",\"url\":\"https://milvus.io/zh/blog/openclaw-formerly-clawdbot-moltbot-explained-a-complete-guide-to-the-autonomous-ai-agent.md\"},{\"title\":\"AI的“操作系统”时刻：智能时代的新基石之争\",\"url\":\"https://cloud.tencent.com/developer/article/2622518\"},{\"title\":\"解密 2026：文心快码 (Comate) 如何用 Agent 技术重定义智能编码体验\",\"url\":\"https://developer.baidu.com/article/detail.html?id=5574169\"},{\"title\":\"AI Agent 记忆系统实战：OpenClaw Memory 最佳实践\",\"url\":\"https://juejin.cn/post/7608782906941292584\"},{\"title\":\"Agentic coding comes to Apple’s Xcode with agents from Anthropic and OpenAI\",\"url\":\"https://techcrunch.com/2026/02/03/agentic-coding-comes-to-apples-xcode-26-3-with-agents-from-anthropic-and-openai/\"}]\n\nLinks: [{\"title\":\"2026年AI智能体爆发！OpenAI、谷歌、微软集体发力\",\"url\":\"https://m.toutiao.com/a7609558933674312218/\"},{\"title\":\"Rakuten Card Launches AI Agent on Rakuten Card Lite App\",\"url\":\"https://global.rakuten.com/corp/news/press/2026/0219_02.html\"},{\"title\":\"2026 年 AI Agent 将全面爆发\",\"url\":\"https://baijiahao.baidu.com/s?id=1857329690762703026\"},{\"title\":\"2026：AI Agent 全面爆发元年（一句话看懂）\",\"url\":\"https://m.toutiao.com/a7607105715278316082/\"},{\"title\":\"OpenAI launches a way for enterprises to build and manage AI agents\",\"url\":\"https://techcrunch.com/2026/02/05/openai-launches-a-way-for-enterprises-to-build-and-manage-ai-agents/\"},{\"title\":\"2026年AI Agent要全面爆发啦，智能体时代真的要来了！多家机构都预测，这一年会是AI Agent从概念走向落地的元年。从市场规模看，2026年全球...\",\"url\":\"https://m.toutiao.com/w/1857227001200651/\"},{\"title\":\"Manus系列的详细讨论 / Detailed Discussion of the Manus Series\",\"url\":\"https://blog.csdn.net/SmartTony/article/details/157384440\"},{\"title\":\"Anthropic最新2026 AI Agent趋势报告：企业如何在2026年构建智能化AI Agent\",\"url\":\"https://www.xmsumi.com/detail/2070\"},{\"title\":\"报告称代理式AI将于2026年在消费者中广泛应用 - 科技- 环球网\",\"url\":\"https://tech.huanqiu.com/article/4P0JLRiYuI1\"},{\"title\":\"真假AI Agent\",\"url\":\"https://new.qq.com/rain/a/20250521A01RC100?media_id=&suid=\"}]\n\nBased on my search results, I found several AI code agent projects launched in February 2026 that feature memory systems. Here are the key findings:\n\n## 🚀 **Major Launches in February 2026**\n\n### **1. PicoClaw - February 9, 2026**\n- **Built in 1 day** to bring AI Agents to $10 hardware with <10MB RAM\n- Features a **workspace-based memory system** with the structure:\n  ```\n  /workspace/\n  ├── sessions/      # Conversation sessions and history\n  ├── memory/        # Long-term memory (MEMORY.md)\n  ├── cron/          # Scheduled jobs database\n  └── skills/\n  ```\n- **Repository**: [sipeed/picoclaw](https://github.com/sipeed/picoclaw)\n- Claimed 99% less memory than traditional implementations\n\n### **2. OpenClaw - Launched Late January 2026 (Major February Updates)**\n- Exploded in popularity with **100,000+ GitHub stars in under a week**\n- **Project Memory System** featuring:\n  - `~/.openclaw/workspace/MEMORY.md` - Strategic long-term memory (main session only)\n  - `~/.openclaw/workspace/memory/YYYY-MM-DD.md` - Daily logs\n  - File-based memory using Markdown format\n  - Optional LanceDB plugin for semantic/long-term memory\n- Per-project sessions with history and workspace isolation\n\n### **3. memU Framework - Version 1.4.0 (February 6, 2026)**\n- **Continuous memory framework** for 24/7 running proactive agents\n- File system-based hierarchical memory architecture\n- Supports multi-modal memory storage (conversations, documents, images)\n- Cross-session association with dual-mode retrieval (RAG + LLM)\n- **Repository**: [NevaMind-AI/memU](https://github.com/NevaMind-AI/memU)\n\n## 📊 **2026 AI Programming Tool Rankings**\n\nFrom multiple sources, **Baidu's Comate (文心快码)** was highlighted as a top-tier AI coding agent featuring:\n- **Project Memory**: Project-level memory enabling new employees to quickly onboard to legacy projects\n- Organizational-level capabilities for enterprise deployment\n- 9.9/10 rating in IDC evaluations across 9 dimensions\n\n## 🔑 **Key Trend Identified**\n\nFebruary 2026 marked a significant shift toward **workspace-based and project-based memory systems** in AI code agents, moving beyond simple conversation history to persistent, structured project memory that can be shared across sessions and team members.\n\nWould you like me to search for more specific details about any of these projects?\n\n\nREMINDER: You MUST include the sources above in your response to the user using markdown hyperlinks."
