"AI CI/CD agent\",\n    \"sources\": [\"GitHub Blog\"],\n    \"community_quotes\": [\n      \"Automate repository tasks with AI agents\",\n      \"Augments existing CI/CD rather than replacing it\",\n      \"Continuous AI works in conjunction with CI/CD\"\n    ]\n  },\n  {\n    \"name\": \"Qwen Code\",\n    \"url\": \"https://github.com/QwenLM/qwen-code\",\n    \"description\": \"Open-source terminal-based AI coding agent optimized for Qwen3-Coder models. Forked from Gemini CLI, it provides repository-level code understanding, editing, generation, and automated Git operations. Command-line interface for developers who prefer terminal workflows.\",\n    \"release_date\": \"2026-02-16\",\n    \"category\": \"AI coding CLI\",\n    \"sources\": [\"GitHub\", \"Aliyun\"],\n    \"community_quotes\": [\n      \"Terminal-based AI coding agent\",\n      \"Optimized for Qwen3-Coder models\",\n      \"Repository-level code understanding and editing\",\n      \"Open-source alternative to Claude Code\"\n    ]\n  },\n  {\n    \"name\": \"Superpowers\",\n    \"url\": \"https://github.com/obra/superpowers\",\n    \"description\": \"AI coding assistant skill framework and development methodology that standardizes AI coding agent workflows. Breaks down software development into composable skill modules (brainstorming, TDD, code review) and supports integration with Claude Code, Cursor, and Codex.\",\n    \"release_date\": \"2026-01-23\",\n    \"category\": \"AI coding framework\",\n    \"sources\": [\"GitHub\", \"CSDN\"],\n    \"community_quotes\": [\n      \"Standardizes AI coding agent development workflows\",\n      \"Composable skill modules for software development\",\n      \"55k stars on GitHub\",\n      \"Integrates with Claude Code, Cursor, and Codex\"\n    ]\n  },\n  {\n    \"name\": \"Apple Xcode 26.3\",\n    \"url\": \"https://developer.apple.com/xcode/\",\n    \"description\": \"Major update to Apple's IDE introducing native agentic coding capabilities. Integrates Anthropic's Claude Agent and OpenAI's Codex directly into Xcode with MCP (Model Context Protocol) support. Agents can access project context, modify files, and verify visual output in SwiftUI previews.\",\n    \"release_date\": \"2026-02-22\",\n    \"category\": \"AI IDE integration\",\n    \"sources\": [\"Apple\", \"InfoQ\", \"TechCrunch\"],\n    \"community_quotes\": [\n      \"First major IDE to ship with built-in agentic coding\",\n      \"Native integration of Claude Agent and OpenAI Codex\",\n      \"MCP support for extensible agent integration\",\n      \"Agents can verify SwiftUI visual output\"\n    ]\n  },\n  {\n    \"name\": \"OpenAI Codex macOS App\",\n    \"url\": \"https://openai.com/codex-macos\",\n    \"description\": \"Standalone macOS application for agentic coding released February 2, 2026. Features multi-agent collaboration, agent skills system, scheduled task execution, work tree support, and seamless integration with CLI and IDE plugins.\",\n    \"release_date\": \"2026-02-02\",\n    \"category\": \"AI coding application\",\n    \"sources\": [\"TechCrunch\", \"OpenAI\"],\n    \"community_quotes\": [\n      \"Native macOS app for agentic coding\",\n      \"Multi-agent collaboration without conflicts\",\n      \"Agent skills system for specialized capabilities\",\n      \"Work tree support for parallel repository operations\"\n    ]\n  },\n  {\n    \"name\": \"PicoClaw\",\n    \"url\": \"https://github.com/sipeed/picoclaw\",\n    \"description\": \"Ultra-lightweight AI agent framework built in 1 day for $10 hardware with <10MB RAM. Features workspace-based memory system with sessions, long-term memory (MEMORY.md), and scheduled jobs database. 99% less memory than traditional implementations.\",\n    \"release_date\": \"2026-02-09\",\n    \"category\": \"open-source AI agent\",\n    \"sources\": [\"GitHub\"],\n    \"community_quotes\": [\n      \"Built in 1 day for $10 hardware\",\n      \"99% less memory than traditional implementations\",\n      \"Workspace-based memory system\",\n      \"Runs on <10MB RAM\"\n    ]\n  },\n  {\n    \"name\": \"Qwen 3.5 and Qwen3-Coder-Next\",\n    \"url\": \"https://github.com/QwenLM/Qwen3.5\",\n    \"description\": \"397B Mixture-of-Experts model with 17B active parameters and 262K native context (extensible to 1M). Released February 16, 2026. Qwen3-Coder-Next is optimized for programming agents and local development with enhanced code execution at low inference costs.\",\n    \"release_date\": \"2026-02-16\",\n    \"category\": \"open-source AI model\",\n    \"sources\": [\"GitHub\", \"Qwen AI\"],\n    \"community_quotes\": [\n      \"397B MoE model with 262K native context\",\n      \"Optimized for programming agents\",\n      \"Open-source alternative to proprietary coding models\",\n      \"Extensible to 1M tokens\"\n    ]\n  },\n  {\n    \"name\": \"memU Framework\",\n    \"url\": \"https://github.com/NevaMind-AI/memU\",\n    \"description\": \"Continuous memory framework for 24/7 running proactive agents, updated to version 1.4.0 on February 6, 2026. Features file system-based hierarchical memory architecture, multi-modal storage (conversations, documents, images), and cross-session association with dual-mode retrieval (RAG + LLM).\",\n    \"release_date\": \"2026-02-06\",\n    \"category\": \"AI memory framework\",\n    \"sources\": [\"GitHub\"],\n    \"community_quotes\": [\n      \"Continuous memory framework for always-on agents\",\n      \"Hierarchical memory architecture\",\n      \"Multi-modal storage support\",\n      \"Dual-mode retrieval: RAG + LLM\"\n    ]\n  },\n  {\n    \"name\": \"GitHub Copilot Claude & Codex Integration\",\n    \"url\": \"https://github.com/features/copilot\",\n    \"description\": \"GitHub announced integration of Anthropic's Claude and OpenAI's Codex programming agents on February 5, 2026. Available to Copilot Pro Plus and Enterprise subscribers across web, mobile, and VS Code. Part of GitHub's 'Agent HQ' strategy allowing developers to switch between AI agents.\",\n    \"release_date\": \"2026-02-05\",\n    \"category\": \"AI IDE integration\",\n    \"sources\": [\"GitHub\", \"DoNews\"],\n    \"community_quotes\": [\n      \"Multiple AI agents in GitHub Copilot\",\n      \"Switch between Claude and Codex agents\",\n      \"Agent HQ strategy for multi-agent workflows\",\n      \"Available across web, mobile, and VS Code\"\n    ]\n  }\n]",
